00:33.220 --> 00:36.250
'Twas the night
before Christmas,

00:36.290 --> 00:38.020
when all through the house,

00:38.060 --> 00:40.920
not a creature was stirring,

00:40.960 --> 00:42.990
not even a mouse.

00:43.030 --> 00:48.100
The stockings were hung
by the chimney with care,

00:48.130 --> 00:53.440
in hopes that Saint Nicholas
soon would be there.

00:53.470 --> 00:58.510
The children were nestled
all snug in their beds,

00:58.540 --> 01:02.340
while visions of sugarplums
danced in their heads.

01:04.819 --> 01:07.280
And Mama in her kerchief,

01:07.320 --> 01:09.720
and I in my cap,

01:09.750 --> 01:13.620
had just settled in
for a long winter's nap,

01:13.660 --> 01:16.620
when out on the lawn,
there arose such a clatter.

01:16.660 --> 01:18.530
Yes!

01:18.560 --> 01:22.430
I sprang from my bed
to see what was the matter.

01:24.330 --> 01:29.400
But I heard him exclaim
ere he drove out of sight,

01:29.440 --> 01:31.810
"Merry Christmas to all,

01:31.840 --> 01:34.740
and to all a good night!"

01:40.680 --> 01:42.120
Whoo!

01:51.960 --> 01:53.560
Take care.
Thank you so much.

01:53.600 --> 01:55.430
- Thank you.
- Good night.

02:05.810 --> 02:06.810
Mom?

02:06.840 --> 02:08.240
- Hm?
- Are you okay?

02:08.280 --> 02:09.840
Oh.

02:09.880 --> 02:12.250
Yeah. It's just, uh...

02:12.280 --> 02:14.780
I can't believe
that was the last time.

02:14.820 --> 02:16.250
Honey, we're only moving
out to Long Island.

02:16.290 --> 02:17.520
We can always come back
and visit.

02:17.550 --> 02:19.420
I know. It's just, uh...

02:19.460 --> 02:21.920
I never thought it'd be so hard
to leave this place.

02:21.960 --> 02:24.930
Are you guys sure
I can't convince you to stay?

02:25.900 --> 02:27.530
We talked about this.

02:27.560 --> 02:30.270
Your father and I
aren't getting any younger.

02:30.300 --> 02:33.030
And you, we couldn't ask
for anyone better

02:33.070 --> 02:35.100
to take our place here,
seriously.

02:35.140 --> 02:37.370
Honey, the customers love you,
the employees love you.

02:37.410 --> 02:38.870
You've always done
such a great job

02:38.910 --> 02:41.140
keeping the Christmas Eve
block party going.

02:41.180 --> 02:43.210
That is, assuming you
wanna keep the shop going.

02:43.250 --> 02:45.110
- Yeah.
- Are you kidding me?

02:45.150 --> 02:48.120
This store has been in
our family for over 40 years.

02:48.150 --> 02:50.390
This is practically
your life's work.

02:50.420 --> 02:52.650
Of course I wanna keep it going.

02:52.690 --> 02:55.820
Well, since that's the case,

02:55.860 --> 02:58.290
The Christmas Shop...

03:00.230 --> 03:01.400
is all yours.

03:02.770 --> 03:05.200
I'm gonna miss you guys!

03:05.240 --> 03:07.300
We're gonna
miss you too, sweetheart.

03:44.070 --> 03:45.810
Merry Christmas.

04:06.960 --> 04:09.030
No, I'm serious. Look,
you never know what you're--

04:09.070 --> 04:10.230
Yeah, okay.

04:10.270 --> 04:11.730
Oh! I'm so sorry.

04:11.770 --> 04:13.400
Sorry. Um, here.

04:13.440 --> 04:15.440
No.

04:15.470 --> 04:16.600
Here, after you.

04:16.640 --> 04:18.410
Please.

04:18.440 --> 04:21.380
Yeah, sorry.
Um, hang on. So...

04:23.010 --> 04:25.710
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
No, I think we should, uh...

04:49.540 --> 04:51.670
Don't you just love
Christmas in New York?

04:51.710 --> 04:54.940
Someone woke up on the right
side of the Christmas tree.

04:58.010 --> 05:00.250
Good morning, Toby!

05:00.280 --> 05:02.120
Good morning to you too.

05:02.150 --> 05:03.650
- Someone spiked her eggnog.
- Hmm.

05:05.360 --> 05:07.860
Guys, this is my first day
running The Christmas Shop,

05:07.890 --> 05:10.120
and I am going to make it...

05:10.160 --> 05:12.690
our best season yet.

05:12.730 --> 05:14.100
Okay!

05:14.130 --> 05:17.100
So what are we gonna
work on first?

05:17.130 --> 05:19.100
What do you mean?

05:19.140 --> 05:20.870
It's like you said,
The Christmas Shop is yours.

05:20.900 --> 05:22.300
That means you can change
whatever you want.

05:22.340 --> 05:24.810
Guys, why would I
wanna change anything?

05:24.840 --> 05:27.010
People have been coming here
for 40 years.

05:27.040 --> 05:29.280
Generations have grown up
with this place.

05:29.310 --> 05:31.950
I think it's perfect
just the way it is.

05:31.980 --> 05:34.380
What are we gonna do about the
big Christmas Eve block party?

05:34.420 --> 05:36.950
I mean, your dad
always did the decorations,

05:36.990 --> 05:38.620
and your mom would always
read the crowd a story.

05:38.660 --> 05:41.790
Assuming people even come.
You know sales are down.

05:41.830 --> 05:44.190
Guys, we can handle it.

05:44.230 --> 05:45.890
Erika and I have been
practically running this place

05:45.930 --> 05:47.700
for years anyway.

05:47.730 --> 05:50.130
Come on, there's nothing
to worry about.

05:50.170 --> 05:52.970
Everything's going
to be just fine.

05:55.270 --> 05:56.700
Yeah, I'll look into that
for you.

05:56.740 --> 05:59.510
These figures in front of me
look promising.

05:59.540 --> 06:01.040
Yeah, okay.

06:01.080 --> 06:03.510
Oh, hey, yeah, yeah.
Let me call you back.

06:03.550 --> 06:05.810
All right, yeah. Helen!

06:05.850 --> 06:08.220
- What can I do for you?
- In case you haven't heard,

06:08.250 --> 06:10.690
there's this thing
called "Christmas."

06:10.720 --> 06:13.860
That sounds vaguely familiar.

06:13.890 --> 06:17.690
You sure? 'Cause I'm not seeing
any holiday spirit in here.

06:17.730 --> 06:20.760
Oh, well, I know, I know.
I just, I've been so, so busy.

06:20.800 --> 06:23.100
Yeah, come with me.
I wanna show you something.

06:23.130 --> 06:24.330
Yeah?

06:28.040 --> 06:29.300
Michael.

06:30.470 --> 06:33.170
Oh, is this the new development?

06:33.210 --> 06:35.210
Mm-hmm.

06:35.250 --> 06:39.550
50 stories, 90 units,
full concierge service,

06:39.580 --> 06:42.020
health and fitness spa,
three restaurants,

06:42.050 --> 06:44.220
and an organic supermarket.

06:44.250 --> 06:46.590
Broadway Towers.

06:46.620 --> 06:49.760
Think you can handle it?

06:49.790 --> 06:51.860
I thought Dunbar
was overseeing this.

06:51.900 --> 06:53.460
He gave notice this morning.

06:53.500 --> 06:55.200
He's going over to Weddington.

06:55.230 --> 06:57.600
Wow.

06:57.630 --> 06:59.800
Rich and Chris are still
stuck on this downtown project.

06:59.840 --> 07:02.640
I honestly don't have
anybody else available.

07:02.670 --> 07:05.710
Look, if it's gonna
be too much work,

07:05.740 --> 07:06.870
I mean, we could outsource--

07:06.910 --> 07:09.810
No, no, no, I--
I can handle it.

07:09.850 --> 07:10.910
You sure?

07:10.950 --> 07:13.550
Absolutely, yeah, yeah.

07:13.580 --> 07:17.050
Great. You don't have plans
for Christmas, do you?

07:19.090 --> 07:21.120
Of course you don't.

07:21.160 --> 07:23.260
The way your office looks,
I wouldn't be surprised

07:23.290 --> 07:26.060
if you got visited by
three ghosts on Christmas Eve.

07:26.100 --> 07:28.000
You know.

07:28.030 --> 07:31.630
<i> A Christmas Carol.</i>
Yeah, I get it.

07:31.670 --> 07:34.740
Hey, if you were gonna
take some time off,

07:34.770 --> 07:36.440
take it now.

07:36.470 --> 07:39.440
Find somebody special
to celebrate

07:39.480 --> 07:42.480
before things
get crazy around here.

07:51.050 --> 07:52.850
Thank you for shopping
The Christmas Shop

07:52.890 --> 07:55.790
- and have a merry day.
- Thanks.

07:55.830 --> 07:56.860
Hey, Chuck.

07:56.890 --> 07:59.130
So the folks finally retired.

07:59.160 --> 08:01.000
Yes, but don't you worry.

08:01.030 --> 08:03.800
We are not going anywhere.

08:03.830 --> 08:04.870
Oh.

08:04.900 --> 08:06.830
This is for Parker.

08:06.870 --> 08:08.440
- Aw.
- I know how much he loves them.

08:08.470 --> 08:10.340
I'll see you tomorrow,
Stephanie.

08:10.370 --> 08:12.710
Is there anything for me?
I'm expecting a package.

08:12.740 --> 08:14.180
You shipped it here?

08:14.210 --> 08:16.510
Yeah. My roommate
opens my mail.

08:16.550 --> 08:18.180
Hmm. It's from our landlord.

08:18.210 --> 08:20.180
Uh-oh. You're running
the place one day,

08:20.220 --> 08:24.050
and they're already
raising the rent?

08:24.090 --> 08:27.890
Actually,
they're kicking us out.

08:27.920 --> 08:29.390
Ha ha. Very funny.

08:29.430 --> 08:32.860
I'm serious.
It's a 30-day notice.

08:32.900 --> 08:34.530
It says the trust
sold the building,

08:34.559 --> 08:36.860
and the buyer isn't renewing
any of the leases.

08:36.900 --> 08:38.030
Let me see that.

08:41.539 --> 08:43.169
She's not kidding.

08:43.210 --> 08:46.740
It says our last day's
December 31st.

08:46.780 --> 08:48.980
- Did you get one too?
- Mm-hmm.

08:49.010 --> 08:50.510
They can't do that, can they?

08:50.550 --> 08:51.850
Just kick you guys
out like that?

08:51.880 --> 08:53.650
Well, we're month-to-month,

08:53.680 --> 08:55.250
so as long as they give
a 30-day notice,

08:55.290 --> 08:57.320
they can technically
do whatever they want.

08:57.350 --> 08:59.220
This is my daughter's
favorite store.

08:59.260 --> 09:00.390
She's gonna be heartbroken.

09:00.420 --> 09:02.390
Well, what about Patty Cakes?

09:02.430 --> 09:05.030
You can get coffee
and cupcakes anywhere,

09:05.060 --> 09:07.900
but this place,
it's one-of-a-kind.

09:07.930 --> 09:09.900
Where would you start over
with a shop like this?

09:09.930 --> 09:14.670
Okay, guys, do me a favor
and don't tell my parents, okay?

09:14.700 --> 09:17.510
I wanna be the one to call them.

09:17.540 --> 09:19.340
Eventually.

09:24.250 --> 09:27.420
A toast to my kid brother,

09:27.450 --> 09:29.350
improving the city
one building at a time.

09:29.390 --> 09:31.750
How about we see if I actually
pull it off first?

09:31.790 --> 09:33.590
Will you look at that?
A New York real estate mogul

09:33.620 --> 09:35.560
who's actually humble.

09:35.590 --> 09:37.860
Dad would be proud.

09:37.890 --> 09:39.430
Yeah.

09:39.460 --> 09:41.260
I know it's not Christmas yet,

09:41.300 --> 09:43.600
but we got you something.

09:43.630 --> 09:47.100
Aw, you guys.
Well, I didn't get you anything.

09:47.140 --> 09:48.470
That's all right.
Like she said,

09:48.500 --> 09:50.470
it's not Christmas yet.

09:50.510 --> 09:51.770
Stop it!

09:51.810 --> 09:53.770
- Ah, okay.
- This guy.

09:53.810 --> 09:55.740
Here you go.

09:55.780 --> 09:58.110
Thank you.

10:02.290 --> 10:04.320
Hey, wow!

10:04.350 --> 10:06.420
Whoa! First edition?

10:06.460 --> 10:07.720
Where'd you find this?

10:07.760 --> 10:09.790
A thrift shop in the Village.

10:09.830 --> 10:12.660
Since we couldn't get you
what you really needed,

10:12.700 --> 10:14.330
it's the next best thing.

10:14.360 --> 10:16.560
What is it that I really need?

10:16.600 --> 10:18.170
Doesn't it bother you?

10:18.200 --> 10:21.240
You work all the time,
and you have no social life.

10:21.270 --> 10:23.470
Mike, when was
the last time that you,

10:23.510 --> 10:26.670
you know, took a little time
for yourself?

10:26.710 --> 10:31.450
I appreciate your concern, I do,
but I'm fine, really.

10:31.480 --> 10:34.250
I have someone
that I want you to meet.

10:34.280 --> 10:36.180
- Julia...
- We went to Columbia together.

10:36.220 --> 10:38.150
She's 33, she's lovely,

10:38.190 --> 10:40.960
and she's a lawyer
at a midtown firm.

10:42.890 --> 10:45.260
Just promise me
that you'll e-mail her.

10:45.290 --> 10:47.930
I appreciate the gesture.

10:47.960 --> 10:51.200
I do, really, but I'm fine.

10:51.230 --> 10:52.870
Really.

10:52.900 --> 10:54.400
Oh.

10:56.070 --> 10:59.970
Oh, um, it's the sitter.
Excuse me.

11:00.010 --> 11:03.540
Come on. Work is going great,
you're making decent money.

11:03.580 --> 11:05.850
Don't you think it's time
to start thinking about

11:05.880 --> 11:07.980
settling down,
having a kid of your own?

11:08.020 --> 11:10.020
And give up being Uncle Mike?

11:10.050 --> 11:11.350
Not a chance.

11:11.390 --> 11:13.150
Come on, let's eat.

11:34.280 --> 11:35.380
Hmm.

12:02.870 --> 12:05.570
- Hello.
- Oh, hey.

12:05.610 --> 12:07.680
You just caught me.
I was about to--

12:07.710 --> 12:09.280
I've seen you before.

12:09.310 --> 12:11.880
I don't think so.

12:11.910 --> 12:14.480
At the coffee shop
downstairs, right?

12:15.620 --> 12:18.220
- Oh! Right! Yes, hi!
- Hi.

12:18.250 --> 12:20.220
Can I help you find something?

12:20.260 --> 12:23.560
Well, actually, I'm looking
for a Christmas decoration.

12:23.590 --> 12:25.430
Not really sure if
I'm in the right place though.

12:25.460 --> 12:26.630
Hmm.

12:26.660 --> 12:29.300
I think we might
have a few left.

12:33.100 --> 12:35.870
So are you looking
for anything in particular?

12:35.910 --> 12:38.470
Well, something small.
I haven't had a lot of time

12:38.510 --> 12:40.610
to get out this year
and find anything.

12:40.640 --> 12:42.240
My mother always said
the best ornaments

12:42.280 --> 12:44.880
were the ones
that say something.

12:44.910 --> 12:49.650
Well, how about a snowman
playing the guitar?

12:49.690 --> 12:51.620
- Oh, you like him, huh?
- I do.

12:51.650 --> 12:53.120
Check it out.

12:55.290 --> 12:58.790
<i> ♪♪ </i>

13:00.300 --> 13:02.560
Sounds like his guitar
is out of tune though.

13:02.600 --> 13:04.430
Well, to be fair,
it's kinda hard to play

13:04.470 --> 13:05.830
when your arms
are made of twigs.

13:05.870 --> 13:07.540
Touché.

13:10.110 --> 13:13.140
Wow, this is, um...

13:13.180 --> 13:15.140
this is some place
you got here.

13:15.180 --> 13:18.850
Yeah, well, take a good look
while you can.

13:18.880 --> 13:20.920
You going out of business?

13:20.950 --> 13:22.580
They sold the building,

13:22.620 --> 13:24.590
and they're kicking us out
at the end of the month.

13:24.620 --> 13:26.490
- Well, that's a shame.
- Yeah.

13:26.520 --> 13:29.920
Tell that to the Scrooges
who are kicking us out.

13:29.960 --> 13:32.690
And with business being so slow,
we can't really afford to move.

13:32.730 --> 13:34.360
Well, maybe I could help.

13:34.400 --> 13:36.530
Do you have any experience
in Christmas miracles?

13:36.570 --> 13:39.170
No, but I do have a little
experience in real estate.

13:39.200 --> 13:41.970
I'd be happy to give you
some advice.

13:42.000 --> 13:43.800
I mean, if you want.

13:43.840 --> 13:46.470
- Some advice?
- Yeah, well...

13:46.510 --> 13:48.040
assuming that you've been
a good tenant,

13:48.080 --> 13:50.440
which I'm sure that you have,

13:50.480 --> 13:53.450
I think they could get you
at least a relocation cost.

13:53.480 --> 13:56.150
Hmm, interesting.

13:56.190 --> 13:59.350
Of course, you could
always just fight it.

13:59.390 --> 14:03.290
I'll tell you what.
I'm gonna look at a few things,

14:03.330 --> 14:05.290
and I'll give you
a call tomorrow.

14:05.330 --> 14:06.530
If you want.

14:08.500 --> 14:09.960
Stephanie Nichol.

14:10.000 --> 14:11.570
It's really nice to meet you,
Stephanie.

14:11.600 --> 14:13.070
I'm Michael.

14:13.100 --> 14:14.470
I'm gonna take this little guy

14:14.500 --> 14:16.670
'cause he's got soul.

14:16.710 --> 14:18.310
Great choice.

14:30.520 --> 14:34.890
<i> ♪♪ </i>

14:46.070 --> 14:50.340
<i> ♪ I wanna wish you</i>
<i> Merry Christmas ♪</i>

14:50.370 --> 14:54.540
<i> ♪ From the top</i>
<i> of every mountain ♪</i>

14:54.580 --> 14:58.710
<i> ♪ From the middle</i>
<i> of the ocean ♪</i>

14:58.750 --> 15:03.020
<i> ♪ And the bottom of my heart ♪</i>

15:03.050 --> 15:07.190
<i> ♪ You and I could take</i>
<i> a sleigh ride ♪</i>

15:07.220 --> 15:09.960
<i> ♪ Or bundle up</i>
<i> and build a snowman ♪</i>

15:09.990 --> 15:11.790
Ugh.

15:11.830 --> 15:14.530
Is that in dollars?

15:16.230 --> 15:21.040
<i> ♪ Take my hand</i>
<i> Let's skate away ♪</i>

15:21.070 --> 15:25.270
<i> ♪ Though the cold wind</i>
<i> is blowing ♪</i>

15:25.310 --> 15:29.710
<i> ♪ I feel so warm inside ♪</i>

15:29.750 --> 15:32.910
<i> ♪ I can't shake the feeling ♪</i>

15:44.690 --> 15:47.490
And two eyes made out of coal.

15:47.530 --> 15:49.100
What are you working on?

15:49.130 --> 15:53.300
I'm just looking something up
for a friend.

15:53.340 --> 15:55.870
Take a walk with me.

16:04.510 --> 16:05.510
Morning!

16:05.550 --> 16:07.980
Good morning, Erika.

16:08.020 --> 16:09.350
Late night?

16:09.390 --> 16:11.590
I was looking
for spaces for rent.

16:11.620 --> 16:13.920
- And?
- I don't suppose you have any

16:13.960 --> 16:15.790
rich uncles
I don't know about.

16:15.830 --> 16:17.990
I gotta tell you,
my mom is not gonna be happy

16:18.030 --> 16:19.360
with me moving back in
with her.

16:19.400 --> 16:20.960
We have 30 days
to figure this out.

16:21.000 --> 16:23.200
We can do this. We can.

16:23.230 --> 16:25.500
Yeah.

16:25.530 --> 16:28.500
I know you're
the optimistic one.

16:28.540 --> 16:30.470
That's what everyone
likes about you.

16:30.510 --> 16:32.110
But it's not like someone's
just gonna walk in the door

16:32.140 --> 16:34.640
and tell us how
to save the store.

16:34.680 --> 16:37.180
- Well...
- Did someone walk in the door

16:37.210 --> 16:38.810
and tell you
how to save the store?

16:38.850 --> 16:40.210
All he said was that
he was in real estate,

16:40.250 --> 16:43.120
and he might be able to help.

16:43.150 --> 16:44.550
But it might be nothing.

16:44.590 --> 16:47.390
Nothing?
Stephanie, think about it.

16:47.420 --> 16:49.120
The day you find out
you're getting evicted,

16:49.160 --> 16:52.830
someone just happens to show up
and offers you a way out.

16:52.860 --> 16:54.800
It's like a fairy tale.

16:54.830 --> 16:57.030
Okay, what if I am not looking

16:57.070 --> 16:59.030
for my Prince Charming
right now?

16:59.070 --> 17:00.530
When are you gonna learn
there's more to life

17:00.570 --> 17:02.240
than just eating frozen pizza
at home alone?

17:02.270 --> 17:03.640
And what if I like frozen pizza?

17:03.670 --> 17:06.069
All I'm saying is
open your mind.

17:06.109 --> 17:07.839
Sometimes change is good.

17:13.079 --> 17:15.250
What are we doing here?

17:15.280 --> 17:17.250
You are so terrible
at surprises.

17:17.290 --> 17:19.990
You must've been a real pistol
at Christmastime.

17:21.760 --> 17:25.290
I give you Broadway Towers.

17:26.400 --> 17:28.030
Wait, you bought <i> this</i> building?

17:28.060 --> 17:29.500
- Mm-hmm.
- Trolley Square?

17:29.530 --> 17:32.200
Isn't it great?
The location is perfect.

17:32.230 --> 17:35.070
I mean, it's near the subway.
Park's two blocks that way.

17:35.100 --> 17:37.570
What about the tenants?

17:37.610 --> 17:39.010
Well, you don't have
to worry about them.

17:39.040 --> 17:41.340
They'll be out
by the end of the month.

17:50.750 --> 17:53.590
It's him.

17:53.620 --> 17:55.320
Prince Charming?

17:57.790 --> 17:59.390
So if everybody
gets out by the 31st,

17:59.430 --> 18:01.530
I mean, we can break ground
the first of January.

18:01.560 --> 18:04.100
- Michael!
- Hi, Stephanie.

18:04.130 --> 18:06.200
Break ground for what?

18:06.240 --> 18:09.140
