34:14.500 --> 34:17.040
Steph, what have you
gotten yourself into?

34:18.510 --> 34:19.940
<i> Just let me call you</i>
<i> in a few days.</i>

34:19.969 --> 34:21.610
<i> Everything is</i>
<i> gonna be just fine.</i>

34:21.639 --> 34:25.810
Okay, sweetheart.
I love you. Bye.

34:25.850 --> 34:27.150
Daniel Martin Nichol!

34:27.179 --> 34:29.380
You put that back
right this second!

34:42.730 --> 34:45.199
We brought cupcakes!

34:46.230 --> 34:48.730
Ah, cinnamon swirl!

34:48.770 --> 34:50.469
You didn't have to do that.

34:50.510 --> 34:52.440
Speak for yourself.

34:52.469 --> 34:55.070
Mommy, can I go see
the reindeer?

34:55.110 --> 34:56.580
Sure.

34:56.610 --> 34:59.210
All the press your store
has gotten

34:59.250 --> 35:01.610
- has been great for business.
- Really?

35:01.650 --> 35:04.080
You don't think it might
turn things around, do you?

35:04.120 --> 35:05.120
I don't know.

35:05.150 --> 35:08.620
But I wanted to tell you,

35:08.660 --> 35:10.620
we found a new location.

35:10.660 --> 35:12.830
Really?

35:12.860 --> 35:14.490
Over on 84th.

35:14.530 --> 35:17.230
It's smaller,
but it's got a great kitchen.

35:17.270 --> 35:19.970
We were planning to move
after the block party.

35:20.000 --> 35:22.740
The Blooms found a place too.

35:22.770 --> 35:24.140
Oh.

35:24.170 --> 35:25.940
What about you guys?

35:25.970 --> 35:29.340
- Well, um--
- Stephanie...

35:29.380 --> 35:32.150
you're not actually trying
to fight them, are you?

35:32.180 --> 35:34.880
No, no,
of course not, I...

35:39.350 --> 35:41.590
I better get going.

35:46.230 --> 35:48.830
I didn't think you had
any meetings today.

35:48.860 --> 35:51.030
Oh, I saw you on TV
this morning.

35:51.070 --> 35:54.030
Oh, well, I just wanted
people to appreciate

35:54.070 --> 35:56.000
a good old-fashioned Christmas.

35:56.040 --> 35:57.600
I thought you were terrific.

35:57.640 --> 35:59.340
Really?

35:59.370 --> 36:01.010
You made me wanna run out
and buy an ornament right now.

36:01.040 --> 36:03.580
Well, what's stopping you?

36:06.410 --> 36:10.050
Look, since you're already here,
and you don't have any meetings,

36:10.080 --> 36:12.290
do you wanna lend a hand?

36:13.920 --> 36:15.250
Why not?

36:18.390 --> 36:20.360
Patty came by this morning.

36:20.400 --> 36:22.200
Oh?

36:22.230 --> 36:24.660
Said she found a place.

36:24.700 --> 36:26.870
The Blooms too.

36:26.900 --> 36:28.330
Really?

36:28.370 --> 36:30.370
You didn't know?

36:30.410 --> 36:33.070
Actually, I didn't.

36:33.110 --> 36:35.410
But it must make you happy,
right?

36:35.440 --> 36:36.980
I mean, you're winning.

36:39.410 --> 36:41.150
Stephanie, this is not a game.

36:41.180 --> 36:42.920
It's not about
winning or losing.

36:42.950 --> 36:44.750
It's just progress.

36:44.790 --> 36:47.520
Did it ever occur to you that
maybe things are a certain way

36:47.560 --> 36:49.020
for a reason?

36:49.060 --> 36:51.390
That tradition is
something to be preserved?

36:51.430 --> 36:53.190
Tradition?

36:55.460 --> 36:58.260
What are you doing
tomorrow night?

36:58.300 --> 36:59.730
Why?

36:59.770 --> 37:03.100
Well, I was wondering if...

37:03.140 --> 37:08.240
maybe you would wanna
go someplace with me.

37:08.280 --> 37:10.780
You mean, like a date?

37:10.810 --> 37:15.350
No, no, definitely,
definitely not a date.

37:15.380 --> 37:18.420
So, uh, where are we
gonna be going exactly

37:18.450 --> 37:20.190
on this not-date?

37:20.220 --> 37:22.290
It's a surprise.

37:22.320 --> 37:25.020
Ah. Well, at least tell me
what time I can pick you up.

37:25.060 --> 37:26.890
Oh, you're going to
pick me up, are you?

37:26.930 --> 37:29.300
Yeah. Tradition.

37:29.330 --> 37:30.730
Okay.

37:32.900 --> 37:36.570
Then this is my address.

37:36.600 --> 37:38.270
- I'll see you at seven.
- Okay.

37:38.310 --> 37:40.540
Excuse me, could you
help me find something

37:40.580 --> 37:42.580
for my little girl?

37:42.610 --> 37:43.880
Yeah, don't worry.
I got this covered.

37:43.910 --> 37:45.280
Okay.

37:45.310 --> 37:46.910
Right over here.

37:50.820 --> 37:53.890
It's not a date.
It's just a... you know.

37:53.920 --> 37:55.720
Business meeting?

37:55.760 --> 37:57.820
She's determined to make me
fall in love with Christmas.

37:57.860 --> 38:00.830
Do you ever ask yourself why he
agreed to be there at the shop?

38:00.860 --> 38:03.100
Maybe he felt bad.

38:03.130 --> 38:05.800
Or maybe he just wanted
to give the place a shot.

38:05.830 --> 38:09.000
I actually think that she does
have something special there.

38:09.040 --> 38:11.940
So what's the problem then?

38:11.970 --> 38:13.970
You and I both know
what this is really about.

38:14.010 --> 38:16.580
Oh, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no.

38:16.610 --> 38:18.980
You're the one complaining
about the women you date.

38:19.010 --> 38:19.980
And for good reason.

38:20.010 --> 38:22.520
Michael is different.

38:22.550 --> 38:24.620
He can actually be
pretty helpful...

38:24.650 --> 38:27.090
when he wants to be.

38:28.690 --> 38:31.490
You should've seen her
on television.

38:31.530 --> 38:34.090
Oh, yeah, this is just
a business meeting, all right.

38:34.130 --> 38:36.330
Sure. Come on.
Let's hit the ice.

38:36.360 --> 38:40.300
- Let me show you who's boss.
- Oh, you are so going down!

38:54.080 --> 38:56.320
Not a date,
not a date, not a date.

39:07.930 --> 39:09.730
Wow. You look...

39:09.760 --> 39:11.360
Wow.

39:11.400 --> 39:13.300
So do you.

39:13.330 --> 39:16.640
I mean, hi. Sorry.
Please come in.

39:19.110 --> 39:21.670
Wow, this is some place you got.

39:21.710 --> 39:24.740
What do you get
per square foot around here?

39:27.620 --> 39:29.580
Sorry, I can't turn it off.

39:29.620 --> 39:31.480
I was subletting
from a friend of mine,

39:31.520 --> 39:33.920
and then I just
kinda took it over.

39:33.960 --> 39:36.090
It's so close to the shop.
That's great.

39:36.120 --> 39:38.720
One of the many benefits.

39:38.760 --> 39:40.160
Are those...

39:40.190 --> 39:44.030
Oh, yeah, yeah,
these are for you.

39:44.070 --> 39:46.270
They're beautiful, thank you.

39:46.300 --> 39:48.500
I'll go find something
to put them in.

39:48.540 --> 39:50.140
Sounds good.

39:53.270 --> 39:55.780
So any clue as to where
we're going tonight?

39:55.810 --> 39:57.810
And ruin the surprise?

40:01.120 --> 40:04.180
Oh, hey, I think
I know your cousin.

40:07.050 --> 40:09.920
There we go. You ready?

40:09.960 --> 40:11.820
Lead the way.

40:25.010 --> 40:27.470
It's just
up ahead, I promise.

40:27.510 --> 40:29.240
Okay, I'm excited.

40:29.280 --> 40:30.440
We're here.

40:30.480 --> 40:32.880
Oh, what?

40:34.450 --> 40:35.680
Ooh.

40:38.120 --> 40:39.950
What is this?

40:39.990 --> 40:42.390
- Oh, you'll see.
- Uh-oh.

40:42.420 --> 40:44.020
After you.

40:49.460 --> 40:51.660
You sure we wouldn't be more
comfortable in the back?

40:51.700 --> 40:53.230
Relax.

40:56.340 --> 40:59.370
- You are gonna love this.
- Okay.

41:09.950 --> 41:14.150
♪♪

41:26.070 --> 41:29.170
Dave Koz?

41:29.200 --> 41:30.940
I thought you'd
appreciate it.

41:30.970 --> 41:33.140
Oh, Stephanie.

41:45.750 --> 41:48.050
You know the story
about this song?

41:48.090 --> 41:50.120
No, tell me.

41:50.160 --> 41:53.130
Well, originally
it was in German.

41:53.160 --> 41:54.830
It's called "O Tannenbaum,"

41:54.860 --> 41:56.900
and it wasn't Christmassy
at all.

41:56.930 --> 41:59.370
It was just a story
about a fir tree,

41:59.400 --> 42:02.700
and the fir tree
symbolized faithfulness.

42:02.740 --> 42:06.840
Later, once the tradition of
the Christmas tree got started,

42:06.870 --> 42:08.240
which was the late 1800s,

42:08.280 --> 42:10.740
that's when they added
some more lyrics

42:10.780 --> 42:13.050
and turned it
into the Christmas carol

42:13.080 --> 42:14.910
that we know and love today.

42:14.950 --> 42:17.550
Hmm, I didn't know that.

42:58.290 --> 43:01.190
That was amazing. How did you
know he was gonna perform?

43:01.230 --> 43:03.530
Stephanie!
Merry Christmas.

43:03.560 --> 43:05.530
Oh, it's great to see you.

43:05.570 --> 43:06.930
Dave, there's someone
I want you to meet.

43:06.970 --> 43:09.270
Dave, meet Michael.
Michael, meet Dave.

43:09.300 --> 43:11.440
- Michael, nice to meet you.
- Yeah, great to meet you too.

43:11.470 --> 43:13.610
- Did you enjoy the show?
- It was fantastic, yeah.

43:13.640 --> 43:14.940
- It was really fun.
- Great.

43:14.980 --> 43:16.710
I'm so happy
that you could come.

43:16.740 --> 43:18.910
And by the way, you were
so right about the poinsettias.

43:18.950 --> 43:21.410
Look how great
they look on our set.

43:21.450 --> 43:23.480
- Always happy to help.
- I really appreciate it.

43:23.520 --> 43:25.720
Listen, I gotta run.
Great to see you.

43:25.750 --> 43:27.390
All the best.
Great to meet you, Michael.

43:27.420 --> 43:29.420
- Yeah, a real pleasure.
- I appreciate you guys coming.

43:29.460 --> 43:30.660
- Thank you.
- Merry Christmas!

43:30.690 --> 43:32.420
- Merry Christmas!
- Bye.

43:34.460 --> 43:36.960
Okay, so how do you know him?

43:37.000 --> 43:38.800
- Who, Dave?
- Yeah.

43:38.830 --> 43:41.230
He's been coming
to our shop for years.

43:41.270 --> 43:43.270
Well, when he's actually
in town.

43:43.300 --> 43:46.910
Okay, yeah.
Dave Koz shops at your store.

43:46.940 --> 43:48.940
A lot of people do.

43:48.980 --> 43:52.480
Like I told you,
our shop is special.

44:02.420 --> 44:04.960
So you're really
into music, huh?

44:04.990 --> 44:09.090
Actually, once upon a time,
I wanted to be a music teacher.

44:09.130 --> 44:12.260
Well, I was a music teacher
briefly.

44:12.300 --> 44:13.670
- Really?
- Yeah.

44:13.700 --> 44:16.000
PS 238 in the Bronx.

44:16.040 --> 44:18.670
- What happened?
- Budget cuts.

44:18.710 --> 44:22.810
Apparently music appreciation
wasn't viewed as a necessity.

44:22.840 --> 44:24.980
Oh, that's such a shame.

44:25.010 --> 44:26.680
Luckily I had a fallback.

44:26.710 --> 44:28.950
My dad was really into
real estate for a long time,

44:28.980 --> 44:31.880
so it just kinda came
naturally to me.

44:31.920 --> 44:33.650
Really?

44:33.690 --> 44:35.950
Yeah, while all his friends
were saving up for college,

44:35.990 --> 44:37.460
he bought his first building.

44:37.490 --> 44:40.860
It was a rundown duplex
in Springfield, Ohio.

44:40.900 --> 44:43.530
Wait, you're from Ohio?

44:43.560 --> 44:45.330
Richland County,
born and raised.

44:45.370 --> 44:47.700
I would've thought
you were more of a--

44:47.740 --> 44:50.140
Big city guy?
Not a chance.

44:50.170 --> 44:52.710
Well, I've lived here
my whole life.

44:52.740 --> 44:56.840
Yeah, you strike me as the kinda
gal who likes to stay put.

44:56.880 --> 45:00.510
So do you ever work with him?

45:00.550 --> 45:03.050
- My dad?
- Mm-hmm.

45:03.080 --> 45:05.250
He, uh, he offered, you know.

45:05.290 --> 45:07.050
I think he always wanted me
to follow in his footsteps,

45:07.090 --> 45:09.890
but I just wanted to make it
on my own, you know?

45:09.920 --> 45:12.490
Do my own thing.

45:12.530 --> 45:16.730
Now it's my turn to show you
something cool.

45:16.760 --> 45:17.960
Come on.

45:19.230 --> 45:21.470
Who is that?

45:23.300 --> 45:26.340
Oh, this is one of
my favorite places in the city.

45:26.370 --> 45:27.840
Michael K.

45:27.880 --> 45:30.080
What's up, Randy?
I want you to meet--

45:30.110 --> 45:32.410
- Christmas girl.
- Randy.

45:34.480 --> 45:37.180
You're not the only one
who likes records, you know.

45:37.220 --> 45:38.920
That record you ordered came in.

45:38.950 --> 45:40.920
- I'm gonna grab it for you.
- All right.

45:42.120 --> 45:44.020
So let me get this straight.

45:44.060 --> 45:47.090
You know Dave Koz and Randy.

45:47.130 --> 45:50.100
Well, when my parents
downsized their apartment,

45:50.130 --> 45:53.100
I pretty much inherited
their entire collection.

45:53.130 --> 45:55.400
You could say
that's when I fell in love.

45:55.440 --> 45:57.300
Hmm.

45:57.340 --> 45:59.140
I always felt that music
had the potential

45:59.170 --> 46:01.270
to be honest and pure.

46:01.310 --> 46:03.040
It's not just about
tempo and melody.

46:03.080 --> 46:05.640
It's about the joy
that it brings people.

46:05.680 --> 46:06.780
Culture.

46:06.810 --> 46:09.750
The traditions?

46:09.780 --> 46:11.420
Exactly.

46:13.820 --> 46:15.320
- Here you go.
- Oh, thanks.

46:15.360 --> 46:18.760
Wait, a Christmas album?

46:18.790 --> 46:19.990
Well, okay, first off,

46:20.030 --> 46:21.560
this is not
just a Christmas album.

46:21.600 --> 46:23.430
This is the Christmas album.

46:23.460 --> 46:25.330
Recorded by the Good Knights.

46:25.370 --> 46:26.930
- Oh, you know it?
- Know it?

46:26.970 --> 46:29.130
My grandmother used to play this
for us every year.

46:29.170 --> 46:32.070
I haven't heard
this album in years.

46:33.440 --> 46:34.970
You should have it.

46:35.010 --> 46:36.940
Wait, what?

46:36.980 --> 46:38.310
Yeah, no,
I want you to have it.

46:38.350 --> 46:39.950
No, Michael, I couldn't.

46:39.980 --> 46:43.080
Trust me, if anybody
deserves it, it's you.

46:45.490 --> 46:47.290
Thank you.

46:47.320 --> 46:49.960
You're welcome.

46:53.490 --> 46:55.090
I know Randy's store
is not for everyone,

46:55.130 --> 46:58.960
but for those who love it,
it's special.

46:59.000 --> 47:02.670
My family's shop isn't
much different, you know.

47:02.700 --> 47:05.370
You know Randy
used to be downtown?

47:05.410 --> 47:07.770
One day the building
that he was in

47:07.810 --> 47:09.880
decided they could make more
money with a big box store.

47:09.910 --> 47:12.110
Randy had to move.

47:12.150 --> 47:13.780
I didn't know that.

47:13.810 --> 47:17.480
That space that we were in?
I helped him find it.

47:17.520 --> 47:19.820
All you have to do is ask.

47:19.850 --> 47:26.730
Well, thank you for
a wonderful evening.

47:26.760 --> 47:29.130
Will you be okay getting home?

47:29.160 --> 47:32.660
I just have to pick something
else up on the way home.

47:32.700 --> 47:35.700
Well, good night.

47:36.740 --> 47:38.340
Good night, Stephanie.

47:38.370 --> 47:40.140
Enjoy your record.

48:00.860 --> 48:04.800
<i> ♪♪</i>

48:09.800 --> 48:11.440
Okay, Michael.

48:11.470 --> 48:13.740
If you can help Randy...

48:13.770 --> 48:17.210
<i> ♪ Christmas is coming ♪</i>

48:17.240 --> 48:21.380
<i> ♪ It's that time of year ♪</i>

48:21.420 --> 48:25.180
<i> ♪ When family comes calling ♪</i>

48:25.220 --> 48:29.550
<i> ♪ From far and near ♪</i>

48:29.590 --> 48:33.560
<i> ♪ Hanging the stockings ♪</i>

48:33.590 --> 48:36.760
<i> ♪ By the fire glow ♪</i>

48:36.800 --> 48:39.730
<i> ♪ What could be sweeter</i>
<i> than candy canes ♪</i>

48:39.770 --> 48:43.440
<i> ♪ Under the mistletoe ♪</i>

48:46.110 --> 48:48.440
<i> ♪ I don't remember ♪</i>

48:48.480 --> 48:53.480
<i> ♪ If spring, summer, or fall ♪</i>

48:53.510 --> 48:58.780
<i> ♪ Feeling as warm</i>
<i> every Christmas ♪</i>

49:01.660 --> 49:05.760
<i> ♪ Gingerbread houses ♪</i>

49:05.790 --> 49:07.730
<i> ♪ And sugarplum dreams ♪</i>

49:07.760 --> 49:09.290
Does that look crooked to you?

49:09.330 --> 49:12.160
<i> ♪ This Christmas is perfect ♪</i>

49:12.200 --> 49:13.800
Who asked you anyway?

49:13.830 --> 49:16.400
<i> ♪ A perfect Christmas ♪</i>

49:16.440 --> 49:19.440
<i> ♪ Will be ♪</i>

49:19.470 --> 49:24.340
<i> ♪ You spending this Christmas♪</i>

49:24.380 --> 49:27.010
<i> ♪ Here with me ♪</i>

49:31.190 --> 49:34.650
♪ Bum-bum, bum, bum-bum-bum ♪

49:34.690 --> 49:36.420
Michael?

49:36.460 --> 49:37.820
What are you doing?

49:37.860 --> 49:40.190
Uh, updating your software.

49:40.230 --> 49:42.460
And what's wrong with
the old software?

49:42.500 --> 49:45.300
Nothing.
I love a good abacus.

49:45.330 --> 49:47.330
- I mean, who doesn't, right?
- Funny.

49:47.370 --> 49:49.030
See, but with this program,

49:49.070 --> 49:51.440
it uses your WiFi
to connect your scanners,

49:51.470 --> 49:54.310
keeping track of your
inventory instantaneously.

49:54.340 --> 49:55.670
Speaking of which,
did you know that you're down

49:55.710 --> 49:58.040
to your last two sugarplum
music boxes?

49:58.080 --> 50:00.880
Tradition doesn't have to be
outdated, Stephanie. Come on.

50:00.910 --> 50:03.780
Excuse me, do you have
any cookie cutters?

50:03.820 --> 50:06.150
- We sure do, they're--
- Allow me.

50:06.190 --> 50:08.320
I got this.
Right this way.

50:08.360 --> 50:11.490
Got everything you could
possibly ever dream of.

50:11.530 --> 50:14.260
We've got Santa Clauses,
snowflakes, Christmas trees.

50:17.060 --> 50:18.800
You're glowing!

50:18.830 --> 50:20.870
I am not.

50:20.900 --> 50:23.500
And he certainly seems
to be in a good mood.

50:23.540 --> 50:26.540
He does, doesn't he?

50:26.570 --> 50:28.840
Oh, hey, I was wondering
if you could watch the shop.

50:28.880 --> 50:30.210
I just have an appointment.

50:30.240 --> 50:31.840
Everything okay?

50:31.880 --> 50:34.350
Yeah, just a little something
I have to take care of.

50:34.380 --> 50:35.680
- Sure, whatever you need.
- Take this one?

50:35.720 --> 50:37.480
That feels right.
Excellent choice.

50:37.520 --> 50:39.150
Christmas tree, okay.

50:42.590 --> 50:44.420
So scan the item,

50:44.460 --> 50:48.330
and it deducts it
from your inventory instantly.

50:48.360 --> 50:51.860
Thank you.
That'll be $5.50.

50:51.900 --> 50:53.730
Here you go.

50:56.140 --> 50:57.670
Thank you.

50:57.700 --> 50:59.500
Thank you for shopping
at The Christmas Shop.

50:59.540 --> 51:01.440
Have a merry day.

51:01.480 --> 51:05.510
Okay, you are getting
pretty good at that.

51:05.550 --> 51:06.910
Don't you have work to do?

51:06.950 --> 51:09.710
Hey, what are you doing
Friday night? I...

51:09.750 --> 51:11.850
My brother has this
Christmas party every year,

51:11.890 --> 51:14.090
and I was wondering,
maybe if you're not busy,

51:14.120 --> 51:16.420
you'd like to come as my date.

51:16.460 --> 51:18.290
Date?

51:18.330 --> 51:20.390
We don't have to stay the whole
time if you don't want to.

51:20.430 --> 51:21.960
It's usually
just his co-workers,

51:22.000 --> 51:25.030
which are just a bunch
of boring computer people.

51:25.070 --> 51:26.930
Oh, you make it
sound so enticing.

51:26.970 --> 51:30.800
Well, they have Jenga,
so that's a win.

51:30.840 --> 51:33.040
I would love to,
I really would,

51:33.070 --> 51:36.140
but I have to set up
for the holiday block party.

51:36.180 --> 51:38.210
But if you find yourself
getting tired

51:38.250 --> 51:39.950
of your brother's co-workers--

51:39.980 --> 51:41.750
I'd love to.

51:41.780 --> 51:43.920
I mean, if you would
like me to help,

51:43.950 --> 51:46.250
I could come lend a hand.

51:46.290 --> 51:47.520
Of course.

51:51.130 --> 51:52.560
There she is!

51:52.590 --> 51:54.260
Mr. Cranston!

51:54.290 --> 51:56.160
Oh, good to see you.

51:56.200 --> 51:59.560
So how are the parents
enjoying retirement?

51:59.600 --> 52:01.500
Oh, they're great.

52:01.540 --> 52:04.600
Well, they're lucky to have you
look after the place.

52:04.640 --> 52:05.970
Oh, thank you.

52:06.010 --> 52:09.940
So what do you have
for us this year?

52:09.980 --> 52:11.580
I know it's in good hands.

52:11.610 --> 52:12.940
I will let you know
when it's done.

52:12.980 --> 52:14.910
All right.
Looking forward to it.

52:14.950 --> 52:16.380
Bye, bye.

52:17.780 --> 52:19.480
Is that a message from Santa?

52:19.520 --> 52:22.750
Mr. Cranston is one of our
oldest and dearest customers.

52:22.790 --> 52:24.420
About 35 years ago,

52:24.460 --> 52:26.790
he had an idea
for an ornament he wanted made.

52:26.830 --> 52:28.330
He brought the idea
to my father,

52:28.360 --> 52:30.830
and he created him something.

52:30.860 --> 52:32.500
Ever since, he's been
coming here every year

52:32.530 --> 52:34.270
with a new subject,

52:34.300 --> 52:36.540
something
to share with his wife.

52:36.570 --> 52:38.140
And you make him an ornament.

52:38.170 --> 52:41.710
It could be a moment,
a memory, a milestone.

52:41.740 --> 52:43.710
One year, it was
the birth of their son.

52:43.740 --> 52:46.480
Another, it was
a special vacation they took.

52:46.510 --> 52:48.810
What was the subject
this year?

52:54.350 --> 52:55.820
Their first date.

52:56.820 --> 52:58.860
What are we gonna make?

52:58.890 --> 53:00.860
I don't know.

53:00.890 --> 53:02.260
Oh.

53:06.230 --> 53:08.370
- Something urgent?
- It won't take long.

53:08.400 --> 53:10.340
- Erika?
- Go. We got this.

53:10.370 --> 53:12.470
- Don't we?
- Absolutely.

53:12.510 --> 53:13.670
Thanks.

53:18.910 --> 53:22.080
686 square feet.

53:22.120 --> 53:23.920
The building's
just been renovated.

53:23.950 --> 53:25.950
There is tremendous
foot traffic here.

53:25.990 --> 53:28.120
Great visibility.

53:28.160 --> 53:30.320
It's very nice.

53:30.360 --> 53:32.660
So what is it you say you do?

53:32.690 --> 53:35.260
Uh, retail. Our family--

53:35.300 --> 53:38.560
Well, I own a Christmas shop
on the Upper West Side.

53:38.600 --> 53:40.770
I think I saw that on the news.

53:40.800 --> 53:43.100
Didn't Helen MacLaine
buy that building?

53:43.140 --> 53:46.570
Yep, that's the one.

53:46.610 --> 53:48.670
I'm curious,
what is it your store does

53:48.710 --> 53:50.310
for the rest of the year?

53:50.340 --> 53:51.640
What do you mean?

53:51.680 --> 53:54.580
Well, when
it's not Christmastime.

53:54.620 --> 53:57.780
Oh, well, we sell decorations
for other holidays as well.

53:57.820 --> 54:01.520
St. Patrick's Day,
Valentine's Day, Easter.

54:01.560 --> 54:02.790
Oh, um...

54:04.960 --> 54:06.630
- Ms. Nichol.
- Mm-hmm?

54:06.660 --> 54:08.790
I'm going to be
very honest with you.

54:08.830 --> 54:11.300
The people
that own this property,

54:11.330 --> 54:13.100
they were looking for something

54:13.130 --> 54:16.030
with a little more
ongoing potential,

54:16.070 --> 54:19.770
like a juice bar
or a yoga studio.

54:19.810 --> 54:21.570
Right.

54:23.040 --> 54:25.480
Of course.

54:25.510 --> 54:28.180
You never know
until you try, right?

54:28.220 --> 54:31.550
I, um, I do have a property
in Jersey City.

54:31.590 --> 54:34.450
That might be a little more
up your alley.

54:34.490 --> 54:38.020
Yeah. I'll think about it.

55:03.450 --> 55:05.050
<i>Hello?</i>

55:05.090 --> 55:07.050
It's me.

55:07.090 --> 55:09.520
Hey, your father and I
are in the middle of a game.

55:09.560 --> 55:11.760
He thinks Kringle
is a real word.

55:11.790 --> 55:13.430
It is a real word!

55:13.460 --> 55:15.090
What's going on?

55:15.130 --> 55:16.830
<i> I don't think I can do it.</i>

55:16.860 --> 55:18.230
Do what, sweetheart?

55:18.270 --> 55:21.000
Save the shop.

55:21.030 --> 55:24.870
<i> I tried, Mom, I really did.</i>

55:24.910 --> 55:26.600
The shop just doesn't
make enough money

55:26.640 --> 55:28.570
to qualify for a new lease.

55:28.610 --> 55:30.340
Oh, honey.

55:30.380 --> 55:33.580
<i> I know how important the shop</i>
<i> is to you and Dad,</i>

55:33.610 --> 55:37.120
but it just, it just seems
like everything's changing.

55:37.150 --> 55:40.720
And I'm trying so hard
to hold onto it,

55:40.750 --> 55:42.220
<i> to preserve something</i>
<i> that means so much</i>

55:42.260 --> 55:43.520
<i> to so many people.</i>

55:43.560 --> 55:45.520
Well, you did
the best you could.

55:45.560 --> 55:48.260
Then why do I feel like
I'm letting you down?

55:48.300 --> 55:50.530
<i> Not just you and Dad,</i>

55:50.560 --> 55:55.300
but Erika and Toby
and all the customers.

55:55.340 --> 55:57.140
Honey, you didn't let us down.

55:57.170 --> 56:00.270
We don't need the shop to be
happy. We have each other.

56:00.310 --> 56:02.870
<i> That's what's important.</i>
<i> That's all we've ever needed.</i>

56:02.910 --> 56:04.240
<i> And you know what?</i>

56:04.280 --> 56:06.480
We'll make new traditions.

56:06.510 --> 56:09.580
<i> Erika and Toby will be fine.</i>
<i> The customers will be fine.</i>

56:09.620 --> 56:13.490
<i> And your father and I</i>
<i> will always be proud of you,</i>

56:13.520 --> 56:17.660
<i> no matter what, okay?</i>

56:17.690 --> 56:19.490
<i> Now Christmas is in four days.</i>

56:19.530 --> 56:23.760
You make it the best four days
that shop has ever seen, okay?

56:23.800 --> 56:25.830
Okay.

56:25.870 --> 56:27.570
You got it.

56:34.640 --> 56:36.240
Well?

56:36.280 --> 56:38.910
It isn't here,
but I gave you "frankincense."

56:38.950 --> 56:41.380
Frankincense is a word.

56:44.120 --> 56:46.080
- Dan.
- Hmm?

56:46.120 --> 56:47.920
What are we doing here?

56:47.950 --> 56:49.620
Playing a game.

56:49.660 --> 56:50.960
No, I mean here.

56:50.990 --> 56:54.190
- I mean, don't you feel--
- Bored?

56:54.230 --> 56:56.260
I miss the city.

56:56.300 --> 56:58.530
We don't belong here.

56:58.570 --> 57:00.530
We belong there,
with our daughter.

57:00.570 --> 57:03.330
Well, then let's go home.

57:05.170 --> 57:06.440
Really?

57:06.470 --> 57:07.840
Yeah.

57:07.870 --> 57:09.440
Oh!

57:09.480 --> 57:11.710
I love you!

57:11.750 --> 57:13.340
Does this mean
I can order bacon again?

57:13.380 --> 57:15.580
- No.
- No?

57:23.090 --> 57:24.690
All right, well, yeah,

57:24.720 --> 57:27.530
let's get those over
to the office, all right?

57:27.560 --> 57:30.460
- Okay, thank you.
- Yes, sir.

57:37.500 --> 57:39.370
Helen, what are you
doing here?

57:39.410 --> 57:41.140
Everything proceeding
on schedule?

57:41.170 --> 57:43.410
Yeah, don't worry.
They'll be out on time

57:43.440 --> 57:45.210
if that's what you're
concerned about.

57:45.250 --> 57:47.410
Is that what you think?

57:47.450 --> 57:49.210
They're good people.

57:49.250 --> 57:51.120
I'm sure they are.

57:56.860 --> 58:01.230
Michael, I realize that I put
a lot of responsibility

58:01.260 --> 58:02.760
on your shoulders,

58:02.800 --> 58:05.430
but I haven't heard from you
in three days,

58:05.470 --> 58:10.070
so I wanted to come down here
and see how you were doing.

58:10.100 --> 58:13.400
Look, the permits have been
submitted and approved.

58:13.440 --> 58:15.210
They think that
they can preserve

58:15.240 --> 58:16.910
some of the facade
as a focal point,

58:16.940 --> 58:18.940
if you're still interested.

58:18.980 --> 58:23.410
I wanted to come down
to see how you were doing.

58:25.950 --> 58:27.220
Excuse me, can you help me
find something?

58:27.250 --> 58:29.590
Oh, of course, yeah.
Excuse me.

58:31.830 --> 58:34.790
So are you looking for
something for your parents?

58:34.830 --> 58:36.030
No, my teacher.

58:36.060 --> 58:37.460
Oh, what grade are you in?

58:37.500 --> 58:39.400
Third grade,
but we're leaving.

58:39.430 --> 58:40.770
Oh?

58:40.800 --> 58:44.070
My family and I
are moving to Seattle.

58:44.100 --> 58:45.300
Seattle's a nice place.

58:45.340 --> 58:47.210
I don't wanna move.

58:47.240 --> 58:49.270
You know,
when I was about your age,

58:49.310 --> 58:50.810
I had to move too.

58:50.840 --> 58:51.880
To Seattle?

58:51.910 --> 58:54.310
No, it was to Ohio.

58:54.350 --> 58:55.750
My dad got a job there,

58:55.780 --> 58:57.780
so we had to pack up
everything that we owned

58:57.820 --> 58:59.750
and put it into these boxes

58:59.790 --> 59:01.320
and get it all onto
a great big truck.

59:01.350 --> 59:03.290
My mom let me
pack my own toys.

59:03.320 --> 59:06.390
Yeah? Well, you know
what happened after that?

59:06.430 --> 59:08.260
I met my best friend Jack.

59:08.300 --> 59:11.160
Yeah. We went everywhere
together. He was the best.

59:11.200 --> 59:13.460
We went to the movies,
we went to the library.

59:13.500 --> 59:15.800
He even taught my brother
and I how to play hockey.

59:15.840 --> 59:18.970
- So guess what happened next?
- What?

59:19.010 --> 59:21.470
I wasn't sad anymore.
In fact, it turned out to be

59:21.510 --> 59:23.780
one of the best things
that ever happened to me.

59:23.810 --> 59:25.780
I don't want Ms. Hill
to forget me.

59:25.810 --> 59:27.780
- Is that your teacher?
- Yeah.

59:27.810 --> 59:29.350
Do you have like, um...

59:29.380 --> 59:31.950
Do you have like a favorite
memory from your class?

59:31.990 --> 59:35.520
Last week she read us a book
about a gingerbread family.

59:35.560 --> 59:37.320
Yeah? Hmm.

59:41.230 --> 59:42.360
Come with me.

59:42.400 --> 59:45.330
I got the perfect thing for you.

59:47.870 --> 59:49.270
What do you think?

59:49.300 --> 59:50.870
It's just like the one
in the book!

59:50.900 --> 59:52.600
Well, then I'm sure
she'll love it.

59:52.640 --> 59:53.670
How much?

59:53.710 --> 59:54.970
Tell you what.

59:55.010 --> 59:57.480
If you give Seattle
a fair shot,

59:57.510 --> 01:00:00.140
it's on me, okay?

01:00:00.180 --> 01:00:02.780
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.

01:00:10.160 --> 01:00:11.560
Your boss left.

01:00:11.590 --> 01:00:13.060
Ah, that's too bad.

01:00:15.400 --> 01:00:17.130
So that was very sweet.

01:00:17.160 --> 01:00:19.960
Oh, well, you know,
somebody once told me

01:00:20.000 --> 01:00:23.670
that the best ornaments
are the ones that say things.

01:00:23.700 --> 01:00:25.400
Hmm.

01:00:25.440 --> 01:00:28.540
Sounds like someone very wise.

01:00:28.580 --> 01:00:29.940
And special.

01:00:32.910 --> 01:00:35.650
- Uh, speaking of ornaments...
- Yes?

01:00:35.680 --> 01:00:38.750
I believe that we have
a first date ornament to make.

01:00:38.790 --> 01:00:41.050
- Oh, we do, do we?
- Mm-hmm.

01:00:41.090 --> 01:00:43.550
Come on, open this letter up.
Let's see what it says.

01:00:47.930 --> 01:00:49.990
<i>I remember</i>
<i> the very first date</i>

01:00:50.030 --> 01:00:52.460
<i> Mary and I ever had.</i>

01:00:52.500 --> 01:00:55.030
<i> I was working as a fry cook</i>

01:00:55.070 --> 01:00:58.800
<i> in a little diner</i>
<i> in San Francisco.</i>

01:00:58.840 --> 01:01:03.370
<i> One late December night,</i>
<i> I'm in the back.</i>

01:01:03.410 --> 01:01:08.150
<i> Someone's crooning</i>
<i> "Jingle Bells" on the jukebox.</i>

01:01:08.180 --> 01:01:11.220
<i> And that's when Mary walked i.</i>

01:01:11.250 --> 01:01:13.750
<i> Her eyes sparkled</i>
<i> like ice crystals</i>

01:01:13.790 --> 01:01:15.990
<i> on fresh fallen snow.</i>

01:01:16.020 --> 01:01:18.920
<i> Her smile lit up</i>
<i> the whole room.</i>

01:01:18.960 --> 01:01:23.030
<i> We must've talked for hours.</i>

01:01:23.060 --> 01:01:25.430
<i> And then I asked her to dance.</i>

01:01:25.470 --> 01:01:29.330
<i> Right there in the middle</i>
<i> of that greasy diner.</i>

01:01:29.370 --> 01:01:30.940
<i> Hmm!</i>

01:01:30.970 --> 01:01:35.370
<i> And I knew I would be</i>
<i> dancing with this woman</i>

01:01:35.410 --> 01:01:38.180
<i> for the rest of my life.</i>

01:01:41.880 --> 01:01:44.250
- Hmm.
- Oh, I got it.

01:02:12.780 --> 01:02:14.580
Do you wanna help?

01:02:14.610 --> 01:02:17.580
I'm not really
the artistic type.

01:02:17.620 --> 01:02:20.120
Come on, this is your idea.

01:02:20.150 --> 01:02:22.120
Grab me a brush.

01:02:22.160 --> 01:02:23.450
Tiny one.

01:02:23.490 --> 01:02:24.660
Uh, other one.

01:02:25.630 --> 01:02:27.190
Bingo.

01:02:27.230 --> 01:02:28.790
Okay, here.

01:02:28.830 --> 01:02:32.260
Okay, now dip lightly.

01:02:34.000 --> 01:02:35.430
Okay.

01:02:35.470 --> 01:02:38.400
And then make a circle
right in the middle.

01:02:41.440 --> 01:02:44.740
- All right, not bad.
- Hmm!

01:02:44.780 --> 01:02:46.880
You know, I think this
could use some glitter.

01:02:46.910 --> 01:02:48.780
And you said you weren't
the artistic type.

01:02:48.820 --> 01:02:49.950
When in Rome...

01:02:49.980 --> 01:02:51.450
- Right there.
- Yeah?

01:02:51.480 --> 01:02:54.090
- Yep.
- Oh, here? Oop.

01:02:54.120 --> 01:02:55.750
Gold or silver?

01:02:55.790 --> 01:02:58.020
- Hmm.
- What are you thinking?

01:02:58.060 --> 01:03:03.530
That one.
And then sprinkle it lightly.

01:03:03.560 --> 01:03:06.660
No, I said lightly!

01:03:06.700 --> 01:03:07.970
That was lightly.

01:03:15.380 --> 01:03:17.210
Beautiful.

01:03:17.240 --> 01:03:21.110
It is a beautiful night,
isn't it?

01:03:21.150 --> 01:03:24.350
- I mean you.
- Me?

01:03:24.380 --> 01:03:27.190
Yeah, I had no idea
how talented you were.

01:03:27.220 --> 01:03:29.350
Oh, thank you,

01:03:29.390 --> 01:03:33.190
but I've never really
thought of myself as talented.

01:03:36.000 --> 01:03:38.830
Well, here we are.

01:03:38.870 --> 01:03:40.100
After you.

01:03:43.600 --> 01:03:46.470
Oh.

01:03:48.010 --> 01:03:51.040
Oh, my goodness,
look at that!

01:03:51.080 --> 01:03:53.880
That's just beautiful.
Oh, yes.

01:03:53.910 --> 01:03:58.080
That's me,
and that's you, honey.

01:03:58.120 --> 01:04:02.750
Stephanie, this is perfect,
as always.

01:04:02.790 --> 01:04:04.390
It was Michael's idea.

01:04:04.420 --> 01:04:06.690
And it comes with this.

01:04:07.760 --> 01:04:09.860
Oh, hon, look!

01:04:09.900 --> 01:04:12.360
They've even got the record.

01:04:12.400 --> 01:04:14.500
This will look great
on the tree

01:04:14.530 --> 01:04:16.730
with the other ornaments
you've given us.

01:04:19.070 --> 01:04:21.770
And to think all I was
trying to do that night

01:04:21.810 --> 01:04:23.770
was get in out of the rain.

01:04:23.810 --> 01:04:26.880
And I was just
trying to finish up those dishes

01:04:26.910 --> 01:04:30.010
so I could go home.

01:04:30.050 --> 01:04:33.150
And now
we've got all these memories.

01:04:38.490 --> 01:04:41.360
Stephanie,
that's a very special shop

01:04:41.390 --> 01:04:43.090
you got there.

01:04:43.130 --> 01:04:44.830
Take good care of it.

01:04:50.100 --> 01:04:53.870
Oh, honey, this is beautiful.

01:04:59.080 --> 01:05:01.610
The shop made all these?

01:05:03.080 --> 01:05:04.420
They're beautiful.

01:05:04.450 --> 01:05:06.620
And every one is personal.

01:05:21.330 --> 01:05:23.300
Do all of your customers

01:05:23.340 --> 01:05:25.340
have a collection
like Mr. Cranston?

01:05:25.370 --> 01:05:28.140
- Quite a few. Why?
- I was just thinking.

01:05:28.170 --> 01:05:31.740
Where are they gonna go
if your shop closes down?

01:05:31.780 --> 01:05:34.750
Well, tell that
to Helen MacLaine.

01:05:37.050 --> 01:05:38.820
You know what?

01:05:38.850 --> 01:05:40.480
I think I will.

01:05:40.520 --> 01:05:42.590
Wait, really?

01:05:42.620 --> 01:05:43.420
Yeah.

01:05:45.020 --> 01:05:47.090
I'm not gonna let her
close the shop.

01:05:52.300 --> 01:05:55.200
I, uh...

01:05:55.230 --> 01:05:58.100
- We should, uh--
- Definitely.

01:05:58.140 --> 01:05:59.940
Yeah, I think, uh...

01:06:01.980 --> 01:06:03.670
I'll see you tomorrow.

01:06:03.710 --> 01:06:05.140
Oh, yeah,
I'll see you tomorrow too.

01:06:05.180 --> 01:06:06.340
Yeah.

01:06:06.380 --> 01:06:08.250
Have a good night.

01:06:12.190 --> 01:06:13.480
Yes!

01:06:27.530 --> 01:06:28.630
Michael.

01:06:28.670 --> 01:06:30.330
We have to talk.

01:06:33.070 --> 01:06:36.910
This Christmas Shop is unique
and a special place.

01:06:36.940 --> 01:06:39.580
It means so much to the people
in that community.

01:06:39.610 --> 01:06:43.710
I know it's old-fashioned,
but you know what? That's okay.

01:06:43.750 --> 01:06:46.250
Because if you want
hip and urban,

01:06:46.290 --> 01:06:49.020
there is a whole city
out there for you.

01:06:49.060 --> 01:06:55.190
But if you want someplace
that's sweet and magical,

01:06:55.230 --> 01:06:57.930
then shouldn't there be
someplace you can go?

01:06:57.960 --> 01:06:59.830
What are you suggesting?

01:07:01.700 --> 01:07:03.600
Let 'em stay.

01:07:03.640 --> 01:07:05.600
We talked about this.

01:07:05.640 --> 01:07:07.070
You transfer the lease
to the new building,

01:07:07.110 --> 01:07:08.570
give 'em the same terms.

01:07:08.610 --> 01:07:11.510
They're paying 75%
below market value.

01:07:11.540 --> 01:07:13.010
They've been there
for 40 years!

01:07:13.050 --> 01:07:15.010
I can appreciate tradition.

01:07:15.050 --> 01:07:18.680
This company goes back
five generations.

01:07:18.720 --> 01:07:20.080
I mean, my great great
grandfather

01:07:20.120 --> 01:07:22.420
worked along
Reginald Vanderbilt himself.

01:07:22.460 --> 01:07:25.790
Our investors expect a return.

01:07:25.830 --> 01:07:27.960
A return is based on
anticipated revenue.

01:07:27.990 --> 01:07:30.060
What kind of revenue
can I promise

01:07:30.100 --> 01:07:31.800
when I'm giving
my tenants a discount?

01:07:31.830 --> 01:07:33.400
I'm not talking
about all of them.

01:07:33.430 --> 01:07:34.870
I'm just talking about
that one.

01:07:34.900 --> 01:07:37.400
We have full occupancy
at this point,

01:07:37.440 --> 01:07:40.100
and I've got over a hundred
names on the wait list.

01:07:40.140 --> 01:07:42.170
Please.

01:07:43.410 --> 01:07:45.480
I'm sorry, Michael, I can't.

01:07:45.510 --> 01:07:47.550
I can't.

01:07:51.020 --> 01:07:54.390
Then consider this
my resignation.

01:07:54.420 --> 01:07:57.290
Michael...

01:07:57.320 --> 01:08:00.290
If you're gonna kick 'em out,
I'm not gonna be a part of it.

01:08:39.970 --> 01:08:42.430
Oh, wow, Stephanie.

01:08:42.470 --> 01:08:44.569
